GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_JargonPolicy> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_JargonPolicy> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#JargonPolicy> ;
    narr:childCount "41"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "c354f003fe2a54a8d5d3268a64e6f8923cccb163" ;
    narr:narration """This hub collects observations about jargon policy across the corpus — how technical, domain-specific, and product vocabulary is deployed, controlled, or deliberately withheld. The dominant pattern is [internal-audience jargon used without definition](narr:StyleObs_TechnicalJargonDensity): RDF/SPARQL terms, infrastructure acronyms, B2B sales vocabulary, and product-specific shorthands appear across documents assuming reader fluency. A parallel strand tracks [deliberate terminology control](narr:StyleObs_JargonPolicy) — defining terms at first use, using bold to introduce canonical vocabulary, and treating the lexicon as a controlled register. a collaborator's March 2026 review formalized this into [explicit accessibility decisions](narr:Narrative_JargonAccessibilityDecisions): glossary as appendix, first-use definitions, and named entity disambiguation. Alongside these, several children document [hard prohibition patterns](narr:StyleObs_TranscriptBootstrap_VerbConstraint) — \"Do NOT say X, say Y\" — encoding terminology control as rule rather than style. A distinct strand covers [code-switching documents](narr:StyleObs_EnterpriseCustomerDemo_JargonPolicy) that move between internal product vocabulary and customer-facing language within a single artifact. [Scarlet's idiolect](narr:StyleObs_ScarletConversationalWhy) adds a named pattern: jargon names the mechanism, a plain-language clause explains why it matters. Coined terms — [cargo-culting](narr:StyleObs_Cargoculting), [relationship-cadence artifact](narr:StyleObs_RelationshipCadenceArtifact), [vibe coding](narr:StyleObs_VibeCoding) — are observed as deliberate idiomatic choices signaling in-group fluency. The [plain-language exclusion policy](narr:StyleObs_PlainLanguagePolicy) and [intentional jargon split](narr:StyleObs_JargonSplit) represent the explicit counter-pole to density-as-default.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_JargonAccessibilityDecisions> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_8> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_Cargoculting> ;
